- Differential privacy (epsilon ~1.0)
- Region-local state and windowed aggregations (<100 ms)
- Drift detection and observability
- Data residency and governance

## Code Example
```javascript
function addDPNoise(count, epsilon) {
  const sigma = Math.sqrt(2 / epsilon);
  const noise = randn_bm() * sigma;
  return Math.max(0, Math.round(count + noise));
}
function randn_bm() {
  let u = 0, v = 0;
  while (u === 0) u = Math.random();
  while (v === 0) v = Math.random();
  return Math.sqrt(-2.0 * Math.log(u)) * Math.cos(2 * Math.PI * v);
}
```

