## Why This Is Asked

Assess the ability to translate usage into a cost-benefit framework for a privacy-preserving, offline-first sync feature, including storage, energy, and cloud costs.

## Key Concepts

- Data sizing and retention policies
- On-device energy and encryption overhead
- Cloud storage/egress pricing and scaling
- Privacy/compliance considerations and opt-in flows
- Go/no-go criteria and break-even analysis

## Code Example

```javascript
function estimateAnnualCost({clipsPerDay, bytesPerClip, retentionDaysCloud, users, costPerGB}) {
  const perUserMB = clipsPerDay * bytesPerClip * 365 / (1024 * 1024);
  const cloudGB = clipsPerDay * bytesPerClip * retentionDaysCloud * 365 / (1024 * 1024 * 1024);
  const monthlyCost = (cloudGB * costPerGB) / 12;
  const totalMonthly = monthlyCost * users;
  return { perUserMB, cloudGB, totalMonthly };
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you adjust the CBA for user growth and volatility in clip frequency?
- What privacy/consent controls would you expose, and how would they impact costs and ROI?

